{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10",
    "summary": "Source text for Ecclesiastes 10 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:1",
      "text": "Dead flies cause the oil of the perfumer to produce an evil odor; so does a little folly outweigh wisdom and honor.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:2",
      "text": "A wise man ’s heart is at his right hand, but a fool ’s heart at his left.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:3",
      "text": "Yes also when the fool walks by the way, his understanding fails him, and he says to everyone that he is a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:4",
      "text": "If the spirit of the ruler rises up against you, don’t leave your place; for gentleness lays great offenses to rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:5",
      "text": "There is an evil which I have seen under the sun, the sort of error which proceeds from the ruler.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:6",
      "text": "Folly is set in great dignity, and the rich sit in a low place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:7",
      "text": "I have seen servants on horses, and princes walking like servants on the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:8",
      "text": "He who digs a pit may fall into it; and whoever breaks through a wall may be bitten by a snake.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:9",
      "text": "Whoever carves out stones may be injured by them. Whoever splits wood may be endangered by it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:10",
      "text": "If the ax is blunt, and one doesn’t sharpen the edge, then he must use more strength; but skill brings success.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:11",
      "text": "If the snake bites before it is charmed, then is there no profit for the charmer ’s tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:12",
      "text": "The words of a wise man ’s mouth are gracious; but a fool is swallowed by his own lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:13",
      "text": "The beginning of the words of his mouth is foolishness; and the end of his talk is mischievous madness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:14",
      "text": "A fool also multiplies words. Man doesn’t know what will be; and that which will be after him, who can tell him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:15",
      "text": "The labor of fools wearies every one of them; for he doesn’t know how to go to the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:16",
      "text": "Woe to you, land, when your king is a child, and your princes eat in the morning!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:17",
      "text": "Happy are you, land, when your king is the son of nobles, and your princes eat in due season, for strength, and not for drunkenness!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:18",
      "text": "By slothfulness the roof sinks in; and through idleness of the hands the house leaks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:19",
      "text": "A feast is made for laughter, and wine makes the life glad; and money is the answer for all things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:ecclesiastes.10.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:20",
      "text": "Don’t curse the king, no, not in your thoughts; and don’t curse the rich in your bedroom, for a bird of the sky may carry your voice, and that which has wings may tell the matter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
